<%!-- ============================================================
  Docs / Publishing an action pack — author + PR workflow
============================================================ --%>

<div class="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-100">
  <.marketing_nav current={:docs} />

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400">Docs / Publishing</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 md:text-5xl">
        Publishing an action pack
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-zinc-400">
        A pack is a directory of YAML. No SDK, no compiler, no signing keys. Author it
        locally, test against a runner you control, then open a PR to land it in the
        public <.link navigate={~p"/packs"} class="text-indigo-300 hover:text-indigo-200">registry</.link>.
      </p>

      <%!-- Steps --%>
      <ol class="mt-12 space-y-8">
        <li class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="grid h-8 w-8 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-indigo-300 ring-1 ring-indigo-500/30">
              1
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Lay out the pack directory</h2>
          </header>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
            Every pack lives under
            <code class="rounded bg-zinc-900 px-1 py-0.5">
              runner/examples/packs/&lt;pack-id&gt;/
            </code>
            with a top-level <code>pack.yaml</code>
            manifest and a per-action YAML in <code>actions/</code>. Optional
            <code>scripts/</code>
            holds packaged shell scripts for <code>kind: script</code>
            actions.
          </p>
          <pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-black/60 p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-6 text-zinc-300">my-pack/
  pack.yaml                    # pack manifest (see step 2)
  actions/
    do_thing.yaml              # one declared action per file
    do_other_thing.yaml
  scripts/                     # only when you have script actions
    do_thing.sh</pre>
        </li>

        <li class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="grid h-8 w-8 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-indigo-300 ring-1 ring-indigo-500/30">
              2
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Write pack.yaml</h2>
          </header>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
            The manifest declares pack-level metadata + which action YAMLs to load.
            <code>id</code>
            is the pack slug (used in the registry URL and install path).
          </p>
          <pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-black/60 p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-6 text-zinc-300">schema_version: 1
id: my-pack
name: My ops pack
version: 0.1.0
description: Short one-line summary shown in the registry.
vendor: acme
homepage: https://github.com/acme/my-pack

requires:
  os: [linux]
  binaries: [my-cli]      # optional — advertised to cloud; a missing one fails at run time

actions:
  - actions/do_thing.yaml
  - actions/do_other_thing.yaml</pre>
        </li>

        <li class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="grid h-8 w-8 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-indigo-300 ring-1 ring-indigo-500/30">
              3
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Declare each action</h2>
          </header>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
            One YAML per action — the runner refuses anything not in the catalog, so this
            file is the contract between your ops team and the LLM. See the full
            <.link navigate={~p"/docs/action-packs"} class="text-indigo-300 hover:text-indigo-200">
              YAML schema reference
            </.link>
            for every field.
          </p>
          <pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-black/60 p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-6 text-zinc-300">schema_version: 1
id: my.do_thing
title: Do the thing
kind: exec
risk: low

description: >
  One-paragraph human description. Shown verbatim to the LLM —
  write it like a doc string, not a comment.

side_effects:
  - Reads /var/log/myapp/*.
  - Touches nothing.

args:
  - name: file
    type: path
    required: true
    validation:
      allowed_prefixes: ["/var/log/myapp/"]

execution:
  command:
    binary: /bin/cat
    argv: ["&#123;&#123; args.file &#125;&#125;"]
  timeout: 10s

output:
  parser: text
  max_stdout_bytes: 65536

# Optional. Renders on the dispatch form so operators (and LLMs)
# see a real invocation before they fill in args.
examples:
  - title: Tail myapp's error log
    args:
      file: /var/log/myapp/error.log</pre>
        </li>

        <li class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="grid h-8 w-8 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-indigo-300 ring-1 ring-indigo-500/30">
              4
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Test against your runner</h2>
          </header>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
            <code>emisar pack install</code> validates the pack (same checks the runner runs
            at load) and copies it into <code>/etc/emisar/packs</code>. It prints the pack's
            content hash — note it down to pin future installs with <code>--hash</code>. Then
            reload and confirm the runner picked up your version.
          </p>
          <pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-black/60 p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-6 text-zinc-300"># on the runner host
sudo emisar pack install ./my-pack --dest /etc/emisar/packs
sudo systemctl reload emisar
sudo journalctl -u emisar -n 50 --no-pager | grep my-pack

# Re-install pinned to the hash it printed — what registry consumers run:
sudo emisar pack install my-pack --hash sha256:&lt;printed&gt; --dest /etc/emisar/packs</pre>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            In the cloud dashboard, open
            <span class="font-mono text-zinc-300">/app/runners/&lt;runner&gt;</span>
            and verify your actions appear under <strong class="text-zinc-200">Advertised actions</strong>.
            Click <strong class="text-zinc-200">Run</strong>
            on one to confirm dispatch end-to-end.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="grid h-8 w-8 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 font-mono text-sm font-bold text-indigo-300 ring-1 ring-indigo-500/30">
              5
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-50">Submit to the registry</h2>
          </header>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
            Open a PR against the
            <.external_link
              href="https://github.com/andrewdryga/emisar"
              class="text-indigo-300 hover:text-indigo-200"
            >
              main repo
            </.external_link>
            adding your pack under
            <code class="rounded bg-zinc-900 px-1 py-0.5">runner/examples/packs/</code>
            and an entry in <code class="rounded bg-zinc-900 px-1 py-0.5">apps/emisar_web/lib/emisar_web/packs_registry.ex</code>.
            We review for:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            <li class="list-disc">
              <strong class="text-zinc-200">Tight argument validation</strong> — no free-form
              shell strings, paths use <code>allowed_prefixes</code>, and choice args use <code>validation.enum</code>.
            </li>
            <li class="list-disc">
              <strong class="text-zinc-200">Honest <code>side_effects</code></strong> — every
              file/network/process side effect listed. The LLM reads these.
            </li>
            <li class="list-disc">
              <strong class="text-zinc-200">Correct <code>risk</code> level</strong> — destructive
              actions (restart, delete, repair) are <code>high</code> or <code>critical</code>.
            </li>
            <li class="list-disc">
              <strong class="text-zinc-200">Resolvable binaries</strong> — declare what
              the runner needs on the host under <code>requires.binaries</code>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <%!-- Next steps --%>
      <div class="mt-16 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-3 border-t border-zinc-900 pt-8 text-sm">
        <.link navigate={~p"/packs"} class="text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-200">
          ← Back to registry
        </.link>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <.link navigate={~p"/docs/action-packs"} class="text-indigo-300 hover:text-indigo-200">
            Full YAML reference
          </.link>
          <.external_link
            href="https://github.com/andrewdryga/emisar/tree/main/runner/examples/packs"
            class="text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-200"
          >
            Browse on GitHub
          </.external_link>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <.marketing_footer />
</div>
